
=Definition=

Iyad Rahwan:

"In HITL systems, a human operator is a crucial component of a control system, handling challenging tasks of supervision, exception control, optimization and maintenance. Entire fields of study focus on how to best engineer HITL systems to optimize performance, making the most of human judgment while avoiding human limitation, such as susceptibility to information overload, or systematic cognitive bias."
(https://medium.com/mit-media-lab/society-in-the-loop-54ffd71cd802)

